signature_matches.name: link many functions at runtime
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: link many functions at runtime
    namespace: linking/runtime-linking
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe@mandiant.com
      - joakim@intezer.com
    scope: function
    att&ck:
      - Execution::Shared Modules [T1129]
    examples:
      - b7b5e1253710d8927cbe07d52d2d2e10:0x401000
  features:
    - or:
      - and:
        - os: windows
        - match: link function at runtime on Windows
        - or:
          - count(api(kernel32.GetProcAddress)): 5 or more
          - count(api(ntdll.LdrGetProcedureAddress)): 5 or more
      - and:
        - os: linux
        - match: link function at runtime on Linux
        - or:
          - count(api(dlsym)): 5 or more
          - count(api(dlvsym)): 5 or more

signature_matches.name: get geographical location
signature_matches.rule_src:
# generated using capa explorer for IDA Pro
rule:
  meta:
    name: get geographical location
    namespace: collection
    authors:
      - moritz.raabe
      - michael.hunhoff@mandiant.com
    scope: function
    att&ck:
      - Discovery::System Location Discovery [T1614]
    examples:
      - 9879D201DC5ACA863F357184CD1F170E:0x10001A99
  features:
    - or:
      - api: GetLocaleInfo
      - api: GetLocaleInfoEx
      - api: kernel32.GetUserGeoID
      - api: kernel32.GetGeoInfo
      # strings part of requests or parsed from response
      # "geo" and "zip" are too short
      # "region" results in FPs mostly related to memory
      - string: /geolocation/i
      - string: /geo-location/i
      - string: /^city/i
      - string: /region_code/i
      - string: /region_name/i
      - string: /^country/i
      - string: /country_code/i
      - string: /countrycode/i
      - string: /country_name/i
      - string: /continent_code/i
      - string: /continent_name/i
      - string: /^latitude/i
      - string: /^longitude/i

signature_matches.name: check for software breakpoints
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: check for software breakpoints
    namespace: anti-analysis/anti-debugging/debugger-detection
    authors:
      - michael.hunhoff@mandiant.com
    scope: function
    mbc:
      - Anti-Behavioral Analysis::Debugger Detection::Software Breakpoints [B0001.025]
    references:
      - https://github.com/LordNoteworthy/al-khaser/blob/master/al-khaser/AntiDebug/SoftwareBreakpoints.cpp
      - https://anti-debug.checkpoint.com/techniques/assembly.html
    examples:
      - al-khaser_x86.exe_:0x431020
  features:
    - and:
      - or:
        - instruction:
          - mnemonic: cmp
          - number: 0xCC = INT3
        - and:
          - description: INT3 (long form)
          - instruction:
            - mnemonic: cmp
            - number: 0xCD = INT3 (long form byte 1)
          - instruction:
            - mnemonic: cmp
            - number: 0x03 = INT3 (long form byte 2)
      - match: contain loop

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious DNS Query for IP Lookup Service APIs
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects DNS queries for IP lookup services such as "api.ipify.org" originating from a non browser process.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Network Connection to IP Lookup Service APIs
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects external IP address lookups by non-browser processes via services such as "api.ipify.org". This could be indicative of potential post compromise internet test activity.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Regsvr32 DLL Execution With Uncommon Extension
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects a "regsvr32" execution where the DLL doesn't contain a common file extension.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Files With System Process Name In Unsuspected Locations
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects the creation of an executable with a system process name in folders other than the system ones (System32, SysWOW64, etc.).
It is highly recommended to perform an initial baseline before using this rule in production.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Sander Wiebing, Tim Shelton, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Files With System Process Name In Unsuspected Locations
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of an executable with a system process name in folders other than the system ones (System32, SysWOW64...etc).
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Sander Wiebing, Tim Shelton, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: ADS Zone.Identifier Deleted By Uncommon Application
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the deletion of the "Zone.Identifier" ADS by an uncommon process. Attackers can leverage this in order to bypass security restrictions that make use of the ADS such as Microsoft Office apps.
Detects modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, Gleb Sukhodolskiy, Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community, Tim Shelton, frack113 (split)
